## Sprint 1 - Project Setup (1.10 - 14.10)

### Meeting Date: 1.10
**Topic:** Set up Contract

#### Goals for This Sprint
- [ ] Establish team contract and collaboration rules
- [ ] Define team structure and individual roles
- [ ] Identify the core problem
- [ ] Propose initial solution approach

#### What We Did
- **af, al, vp, gi:** Established team contract and communication protocols
- **vp:** Created Jira workspace and initial project structure
- **Team:** Defined individual roles and responsibilities

### Meeting Date: 7.10
**Topic:** Problem Definition & Solution

#### Completed Tasks
- [x] Δομή ομάδας και ρόλοι
- [x] Το πρόβλημα και η προτεινόμενη λύση

#### What We Did
- **vp:** Documented team structure and roles
- **Team:** Analyzed the resource management problem in Greek municipalities
- **af, gi:** Researched existing solutions and gaps
- **Team:** Proposed EfficienCity RMS as comprehensive solution

#### Decisions Made
- Decided to focus on inter-municipality resource sharing
- Agreed on microservices architecture approach
- Confirmed use of blockchain for transparency

### Meeting Date: 14.10
**Topic:** Requirements Gathering

#### Completed Tasks
- [x] Ορισμός χρηστών στόχου
- [x] Χαρτογράφηση ενδιαφερομένων και των στόχων τους
- [x] Συλλογή απαιτήσεων

#### What We Did
- **al:** Defined target user groups (municipalities, citizens, admins)
- **vp, gi:** Created stakeholder mapping and objectives table
- **Team:** Gathered functional and non-functional requirements
- **af:** Prioritized requirements using MoSCoW method

#### Challenges & Blockers
- Needed more clarity on GDPR compliance requirements
- Required additional research on blockchain implementation

#### Notes
- Focus on user needs for municipalities and transparency for citizens
- Security and scalability are critical non-functional requirements

