## Sprint 4 - Technical Architecture (25.11 - 9.12)

### Meeting Date: 25.11 & 26.11
**Topic:** System Architecture Design

#### Completed Tasks
- [x] Αρχιτεκτονική & Τεχνικές Προδιαγραφές
- [x] Components Εφαρμογής
- [x] Frontend Επίπεδο
- [x] Backend Υπηρεσίες
- [x] Pipeline Δεδομένων και Υποδομή Βάσεων
- [x] Επίπεδο Ανάλυσης - Big Data και AI
- [x] Blockchain - Επίπεδο Διαφάνειας Συναλλαγών
- [x] Υποδομή Cloud
- [x] Τεχνολογική Αρχιτεκτονική

#### What We Did
- **af:** Designed microservices architecture with event-driven communication
- **gi:** Specified tech stack for each layer (Angular, Spring Boot, PostgreSQL, ClickHouse, Kafka)
- **af:** Created system architecture diagram
- **gi:** Documented AI/ML analytics approach using Python and Scikit-learn
- **Team:** Defined Azure cloud infrastructure with AKS
- **af:** Specified CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions

#### Decisions Made
- Confirmed microservices with Database-per-Service pattern
- Selected Kafka for event-driven messaging
- Chose Redis for caching layer
- Decided on Prometheus + Grafana for monitoring

### Meeting Date: 2.12
**Topic:** Data Architecture

#### Completed Tasks
- [x] Πίνακας Προδιαγραφών
- [x] Data Schema
- [x] PostgreSQL Schema
- [x] ClickHouse Schema
- [x] Kafka Topics
- [x] Οντότητες Blockchain

#### What We Did
- **af:** Created comprehensive specifications table
- **gi:** Designed PostgreSQL schema for transactional data
- **gi:** Designed ClickHouse schema for analytics
- **af:** Defined Kafka topics for event streaming
- **gi:** Specified blockchain entities for transaction logging

#### Notes
- PostgreSQL handles operational data (users, resources, requests)
- ClickHouse stores time-series data for analytics
- Kafka enables real-time event processing between services

