## Project Retrospective

### What Went Well
- Strong team collaboration and clear role definition
- Comprehensive requirements analysis saved time later
- Agile approach allowed flexibility to incorporate feedback
- Successfully delivered working PoC despite time constraints
- Clear documentation throughout the project

### What Could Be Improved
- Earlier start on implementation phase
- More frequent check-ins during holiday period
- Could have conducted more user interviews for validation
- AI/ML features could be more fully developed

### Lessons Learned
- Importance of thorough upfront analysis before implementation
- Value of continuous stakeholder feedback
- Microservices architecture requires careful planning
- Documentation is as important as code
- Proof of concept helps validate architectural decisions

### Final Outcomes
- **Grade:** [To be determined]
- **GitHub Repository:** https://github.com/AngelosFikias0/Resource_Management_System
- **YouTube Demo:** [Link to be added]
- **Notion Workspace:** https://www.notion.so/2bd9c27e8f1180909629d6343b3cd4b7

### Future Recommendations
If this project were to continue:
- Complete full AI/ML predictive analytics implementation
- Conduct real pilot with partner municipality
- Expand to include more resource types
- Integrate with existing municipal systems
- Add mobile native applications
- Implement advanced blockchain features with smart contracts

